&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: Change Management - Engineer ( TTA)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tungsten TotalAgility (TTA) Developer (formerly Kofax KTA)&lt;br&gt;We are seeking a motivated and detail-oriented Tungsten (formerly Kofax) TotalAgility (TTA) Developer to join our IT Development team. The ideal candidate will have hands-on experience designing, developing, and supporting intelligent automation and document processing solutions using Tungsten TotalAgility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Design, develop, configure, and support solutions within the Tungsten TotalAgility platform.&lt;br&gt;• Develop workflows, business processes, capture solutions, and integrations with enterprise systems.&lt;br&gt;• Create and maintain TTA forms, validation rules, process maps, and transformation modules.&lt;br&gt;• Troubleshoot production issues and provide timely resolution of application defects.&lt;br&gt;• Collaborate with business analysts, operations teams, and stakeholders to gather requirements and implement solutions.&lt;br&gt;• Participate in testing, deployment, and ongoing support activities.&lt;br&gt;• Prepare technical documentation and maintain development standards and best practices.&lt;br&gt;• Support continuous improvement initiatives related to automation and document management.&lt;br&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;br&gt;• Minimum 2 years of hands-on experience developing solutions in Tungsten TotalAgility.&lt;br&gt;• Experience with workflow development, OCR/capture technologies, and document processing.&lt;br&gt;• Knowledge of SQL databases and web services/API integrations.&lt;br&gt;• Familiarity with .NET, C#, JavaScript, or related technologies.&lt;br&gt;• Strong analytical, troubleshooting, and problem-solving skills.&lt;br&gt;• Ability to work independently and collaboratively in a team environment.&lt;br&gt;• Excellent verbal and written communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Certifications Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Tungsten TotalAgility Developer Certification&lt;br&gt;• Additional Tungsten/Kofax certifications are a plus&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Experience in financial services, lockbox processing, or enterprise document management environments.&lt;br&gt;• Experience integrating Tungsten TotalAgility (TTA) formerly KTA with ERP, ECM, or workflow platforms.&lt;br&gt;• Understanding of Agile development methodologies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related field preferred, or equivalent work experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Full-time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Hybrid/Remote&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Competitive salary&lt;br&gt;• Health, dental, and vision insurance&lt;br&gt;• 401(k) with company match&lt;br&gt;• Paid time off and holidays&lt;br&gt;• Professional development and certification support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
